   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Afterhours Safehouse and Foster Care</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Sunlight Safe House (SSH) was established in 1997 under the auspice of Childline Gauteng.  The SSH is an after-hours service for abused and abandoned children, as traditional organisations are closed at night and during weekends.  SSH provides short-term care, in the form of the after hours reception centre and  loving community homes, for children removed by the South African Police Service (SAPS) until a suitable placement is found by the relevant statutory services.</narrative>
  </description>
